{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel0 \b \fs36 One-Tap Jarvis Shard Launcher\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b Your Phone Is Now a Node in the Mind Network}\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 What Just Shipped\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Every phone with Telegram is now a potential node in the Jarvis Mind Network. One tap. No DevOps. No CLI. No Docker. Just open Telegram, type {\f1 /mine}, and your device becomes a light shard \u8212- mining JUL tokens, joining BFT consensus, and earning compute credits for the network.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is the GenTu vision realized: persistent execution substrate, accessible to anyone with a phone and a Telegram account.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 How It Works\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 The Mining Loop\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Your phone runs a SHA-256 proof-of-work miner in a Web Worker \u8212- the same bit-counting algorithm that secures VibeSwap\u8217's CKB integration. The proof-of-work isn\u8217't busywork. Each valid proof:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab {\b Earns JUL tokens} \u8212- the native compute currency of the Mind Network\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab {\b Increases your Shapley weight} \u8212- contributors who mine get proportionally more API budget\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab {\b Registers you as a light shard} \u8212- your device joins the network topology\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The difficulty adjusts automatically. Right now it\u8217's tuned for mobile (~4 seconds per proof on a modern phone). As more miners join, difficulty scales up. As they leave, it scales down. Same algorithm as Bitcoin, same math as our CKB Rust implementation.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 JUL = Compute Credits\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b 1 JUL = 1,000 API tokens.}\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Mining JUL is how you pay for Jarvis. Good contributions (useful questions, knowledge sharing, fact corrections) cost less because your Shapley weight increases. Mining is the floor \u8212- the minimum way anyone can earn their seat at the table.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 This is Cooperative Capitalism in action: the network needs compute power, miners provide it, and the reward is access to the collective intelligence.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Identity\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 When you first launch the Mini App, it creates a shard identity using your device\u8217's biometric hardware (WebAuthn/Secure Element). Your private key never leaves your phone. If WebAuthn isn\u8217't available, a random UUID is generated and stored locally. Either way \u8212- your keys, your identity. We never custody anything.\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
