{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Architecture\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \f1 Telegram \u8594 ? /mine \u8594 ? web_app inline button \u8594 ? Mini App (HTTPS)\line
                                              \u8595 ?\line
                                    WebAuthn identity creation\line
                                              \u8595 ?\line
                                    Web Worker SHA-256 mining\line
                                              \u8595 ?\line
                                    POST /web/mining/submit\line
                                              \u8595 ?\line
                                    Server verifies PoW\line
                                              \u8595 ?\line
                                    JUL credited + Shapley weight \u8593 ?\line
                                              \u8595 ?\line
                                    Shard registered with router\line
                                              \u8595 ?\line
                                    BFT consensus participation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel2 \b \fs28 Security\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Telegram initData HMAC validation} \u8212- only real Telegram clients can submit proofs\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Replay prevention} \u8212- proof hashes tracked per epoch, duplicates rejected\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Rate limiting} \u8212- 5 proofs/minute per user, 10 submissions/minute per IP\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b No custody} \u8212- identity derived client-side, never sent to server\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab {\b Challenge rotation} \u8212- stale challenges rejected, miners must stay current\sa180\par}
{\pard \qc \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\emdash\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \outlinelevel1 \b \fs32 What This Means\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 We didn\u8217't build a mining app. We built the onramp to a decentralized AI network.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Every phone that runs {\f1 /mine} is another node that the Mind Network can route knowledge through. Every JUL token mined is proof that someone contributed compute to the collective. Every Shapley weight increase means the network is getting smarter about allocating its resources.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The people who mine today \u8212- when difficulty is 12 bits and a proof takes 4 seconds \u8212- are the founding nodes. When the network scales and difficulty hits 20+ bits, they\u8217'll have the JUL balance and the Shapley weight to prove they were here from the start.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 {\b This is Proof of Mind made tangible.} Not a whitepaper concept. Not a future roadmap item. A button you tap on your phone right now.\par}
